From fd0a721adbebf1806cfc528287533b8236b40141 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Brandon Payton <brandon@happycode.net>
Date: Tue, 21 Apr 2026 15:48:03 -0400
Subject: [PATCH 35/59] torque: mark kCCBuiltins macro bodies inline via
 InlineDefinition flag
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

The same TorqueMacro may end up emitted as both a kCC body (into
-tq-inl.inc, where the preceding declaration carries `inline`) and a
kCCBuiltins body (into -tq-ccbuiltins.cc, a direct compilation unit
with no preceding declaration). Without `inline` on the kCCBuiltins
definition, the two TUs produce a multi-def link error when both end
up in the same binary.

Prior attempt (commit 905aae7f) fixed this by making
PrintBeginDefinition emit `inline` whenever IsInline() was true, and
SetInline(true) was extended to kCCBuiltins. That worked for the
multi-def case but had a scope bug: IsInline() is ALSO set by the
pre-existing DefaultGetter/DefaultSetter helpers (cpp-builder.h:83-100),
which route class accessors through PrintBeginDefinition. The change
silently prefixed `inline ` to every generated class accessor
definition in -tq-inl.inc — 70 files in the stock 245-file .tq
fileset — shifting the regression-floor sha of stock kCC output from
a5195c02... to 7ca28f71... .

Fix: introduce a separate InlineDefinition flag on cpp::Function,
gated distinctly from Inline. PrintBeginDefinition now emits `inline`
only when IsInlineDefinition() is true. SetInline(true) is reverted
to output_type == kCC (its original meaning). GenerateFunction calls
SetInlineDefinition(true) additionally under kCCBuiltins, which is
the only path that needs the multi-TU ODR protection.

Result:
- Stock kCC output (DefaultGetter/DefaultSetter, all kCC macro
  definitions) is byte-identical to pre-905aae7f output. Stock sha
  a5195c0258fd9af9415e9d41f0c2e38237989c1b over 245-file fileset
  reproduced.
- kCCBuiltins -tq-ccbuiltins.cc bodies still carry `inline` on
  TqRuntime_<macro>_<N> definitions, so multi-TU linkage with kCC
  -tq-inl.inc duplicates is ODR-legal.
- 12/12 Phase 2–4 fixture goldens pass unchanged.
