The CallRuntimeInstruction emission previously wrote
`Runtime::Call<Runtime::kFoo>(isolate, arg0, arg1, ...)`, gated by a
Phase-4 TODO noting that V8 exposes no such static template. Task 5.8
ArrayIsArray surfaced this at array-isarray-tq-ccbuiltins.cc:116 as
"no member named 'Call' in 'v8::internal::Runtime'".

Fix: emit a direct call to the per-intrinsic C++ entry point
`Address Runtime_<name>(int args_length, Address* args_object,
Isolate* isolate)` declared by runtime.h's
FOR_EACH_INTRINSIC_RETURN_OBJECT macro expansion (runtime.h:889-893).

Calling convention:
  - Torque passes `context` as arguments[0] matching CSA's CallRuntime
    contract. Runtime_<name> reads its context from isolate->context()
    via the runtime entry trampoline, so we drop arguments[0] when
    assembling the args array.
  - The remaining arguments are stored in a local `__rt_args[]`
    scoped to a `{ ... }` block so each CallRuntime emission has its
    own isolated args array (multiple runtime calls in the same basic
    block don't collide).
  - For the 0-arg case, pass `static_cast<Address*>(nullptr)` and
    argc=0 — avoids `Address __rt_args[] = {}` which is not valid C++.
  - Return value wrapped as Tagged<Object> and UncheckedCast'd to the
    torque-inferred result type (Runtime_<name>'s C ABI erases to
    Address; the torque type oracle knows the narrower type).

Tailcall path uses the same args-array shape and emits
`return Runtime_<name>(argc, args, isolate);` — caller's Address
return slot aligns with Runtime_<name>'s Address return.

Non-ccbuiltins kCC emission: the stock V8 torque kCC pass did not
exercise CallRuntimeInstruction (grep of torque-generated/ for the
prior `Runtime::Call<...>` pattern outside ccbuiltins comes up
empty), so this change is a no-op for stock kCC output. A future
phase that adds CallRuntime to kCC macro bodies will pick up the new
emission automatically.

This closes Task 5.8 defect (3).
