From c348f41b4aa78eda1eb3327064d0b2aa9769ec4c Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Brandon Payton <brandon@happycode.net>
Date: Thu, 23 Apr 2026 17:56:10 -0400
Subject: [PATCH 57/59] torque: CCGenerator emits return {} on GotoExternal for
 non-void funcs
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

GotoExternalInstruction (cc-generator.cc:~692) emits a label-exit:
  *out_param_i = stack->Pop();
  *label = true;
  return;
This is fine when the enclosing C++ function returns void/never
(macros with signature `macro Foo(...): never labels Bar`). But macros
with a value return type (`macro Cast<T>(...): T labels CastError`)
get declared `Tagged<T> Foo(...)` — and bare `return;` is ill-formed
in non-void C++ functions. Task 5.8 ArrayIsArray surfaced this as 5
-Wreturn-mismatch errors inside TqRuntimeCast_JSArray_1 et al.

Fix: plumb an `external_goto_returns_value_` flag on CCGenerator (set
by the VisitMacroCommon / Visit(Builtin*) emission paths in
implementation-visitor.cc before calling EmitGraph). When set,
GotoExternalInstruction emits `return {};` — value-initialized return
whose value is dead (caller checks `*label` first and skips reading
the return). When unset, bare `return;` continues to serve void/never
returns unchanged.

Three CCGenerator call sites in implementation-visitor.cc now
propagate the function's return shape:
  - VisitMacroCommon kCCBuiltins branch: pass has_return_value
  - Visit(Builtin*) JS-linkage kCCBuiltins branch: pass true (Address)
  - Visit(Builtin*) stub-kind kCCBuiltins branch: pass
    !IsVoidOrNever(return_type)

kCC and kCCDebug emission unchanged — those branches do not call
SetExternalGotoReturnsValue, so the flag stays at its default (false)
and the existing bare `return;` emission is preserved byte-for-byte.

This closes Task 5.8 defect (6).
